v1.8.0 - Split UI for launcher-managed vs externally-launched Claude instances

Windowed claude.exe processes now split cleanly into two lists: the slot
list for processes with --user-data-dir=...\ClaudeSlotN, and a new
External Claude instances section for everything else. Each windowed
Claude appears in exactly one list.

Scanner + classifier (new core services):
  * IClaudeProcessScanner / WmiClaudeProcessScanner - WMI walk over
    claude.exe processes, filtered to those with MainWindowHandle != 0
    to suppress the ~10 Electron child processes per window.
  * IClaudeProcessClassifier / RegexClaudeProcessClassifier - classifies
    a ClaudeProcessInfo as slot (ClaudeSlotN cmdline match) or external.

WMI cmdline enrichment (the non-obvious bit):
  Chromium/Electron's browser-main process reports an empty args list to
  WMI - its --user-data-dir flag is only present on child processes.
  Without enrichment, every windowed Claude mis-classifies as external.
  The scanner now queries ParentProcessId too, walks each windowed
  main's direct children, and when the main's own cmdline lacks the
  flag, extracts --user-data-dir= from any child and synthesises a
  minimal enriched cmdline.

View-model layer:
  * SlotInstanceListViewModel - owns the slot list, relabels
    InstanceNumber with the real slot number from cmdline (not
    sequential enumeration), sorts by slot number, reconciles in place
    (identity-preserving so row-level state survives refreshes).
  * ExternalInstanceListViewModel - parallel design for the external
    list, owns the close/confirm-dialog/kill flow.
  * ExternalInstanceViewModel - per-row VM with smart cmdline trimming
    and uptime formatting.
  * MainWindowViewModel delegates both lists, no longer depends on
    ISlotManager or ISlotInitialiser.

Confirm dialog infrastructure:
  * Views/ConfirmDialog.axaml + code-behind - custom modal with
    severity-coloured accent bar (Info/Warning/Destructive), keyboard
    handling (Enter=confirm, Esc=cancel), public Apply() + Result.
  * IConfirmDialogService / ConfirmDialogService - orchestrates
    dialog construction and modal show, UI-thread marshalling,
    graceful no-owner fallback. Permanent log breadcrumbs at every
    step (construct, apply, show, close) so future hangs are
    diagnosable from the log.

Launcher ownership change:
  * IClaudeInstanceLauncher gains LaunchInstances(int count) which
    owns the full slot-pick + seed + launch sequence. MainWindowViewModel
    now just calls _launcher.LaunchInstances(SlotCount).
  * ClaudeInstanceLauncher ctor now takes ISlotManager + ISlotInitialiser;
    these were previously VM-owned.

Bug fixes:
  * "Instance 1 lol" name no longer attaches to whichever Claude
    process happened to appear first in the resource snapshot - it
    now always binds to the actual ClaudeSlot1 process (the
    enumeration-index approach was the root cause).
  * Mid-slot disappearance (slot 2 closed while 1 and 3 alive) now
    renders correctly as "Instance 1" + "Instance 3"; previously the
    enumeration would re-label slot 3 as position 2.

Tests: 229 passing (up from 162 in v1.7.1). New tests:
  * RegexClaudeProcessClassifierTests - 10 cases (slot/external,
    quoted/unquoted, case-insensitive, empty cmdline, default-profile)
  * ExternalInstanceViewModelTests - 15 cases (cmdline display,
    ellipsis, callback, IsClosing state, CanExecute gate)
  * ExternalInstanceListViewModelTests - 13 cases (empty scan,
    add/remove/update, identity preservation, totals, scanner-throws,
    confirm-yes/no, destructive severity, kill-throws logging)
  * SlotInstanceListViewModelTests - 13 cases (filter, relabel, sort,
    reconcile, middle-slot removal regression, seed state,
    scanner-throws)
  * MainWindowViewModelTestFixture - shared mock graph + CreateSut
    extracted so MainWindowViewModelTests stays under the 200-line
    file limit.
  * ClaudeInstanceLauncherTests - 5 new cases for LaunchInstances
    (slot picking, init-before-launch ordering, returning slots).

Zero warnings, zero errors. Live-verified: slot 1 appears once with
custom name, external PID 65668 appears once, confirm dialog opens on
close click, cancel path honoured (no kill issued).

Docs: ROADMAP tick for split-UI bullet with full design rationale,
v1.8.1 entry for custom app icon work, fresh screenshot at
docs/screenshots/photo_2026-04-18_v1.8.0.png.
